					<div class="content-intro-text">
						<h1>European Institute of Innovation and Technology (EIT)</h1>
													<p class="author"><strong>Author:</strong>
								</p>
																								
													<p class="date"><strong>Date:</strong>
							08/02/2013</p>
																									<p class="intro">Introduction:</p>
							<p>The European Institute of Innovation and Technology (EIT) brings together higher education institutions, research centres and businesses and aims to build Knowledge and Innovation Communities (KICs, a type of cross-border public-private-partnerships). To date, three KICs have been created, focusing on sustainable energy, climate change and information and communication society. The EIT should set up a KIC in 2014 on ‘Food for the future’ that will examine sustainable supply chains. <a href="http://eit.europa.eu/" target="_blank">Click to visit the EIT’s website</a></p><p>(<a href="http://eit.europa.eu/" target="_blank">EIT</a>, 7/11/2012)</p>
						
						
						
						<br/>&nbsp;
					</div> 
					<br class="cl">
				</div> 
				 
			
